Rating: 3
My adaptation, based on other reviews and what I had in the house: 5 garlic cloves, minced 1 tsp coriander 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon 1/8 teaspoon ground cloves 2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder 3 tablespoons peanut butter 2-3 oz baking chocolate, bittersweet a 1-pound can diced tomatoes with juice 14 oz can tomato sauce 3 tbsp chopped prunes 2 teaspoons sugar 4 tbsp honey 1/4 cup orange juice 1-1/2 cups water 1-1/2 tbs canned chipotles Sautee garlic in olive oil. Add cocoa, herbs and spices; cook 1 minute over medium heat. Add wet ingredients. Heat through. Add chocolate, peanut butter, and sugar (use less PB than recipe says - it was a bit too peanut-y; 2 tbsp at most). Simmer over medium until flavors are well combined. Puree with hand held tool. If too thick/rich, add extra water/juice/stock.

