First time making mole (read the authentic version & thought I'd start here after reading the reviews). Took advantage of previous cook's tips... used 1/2 can of drained tomatoes, doubled the peanut butter, added 1-2 t. ea. ground pasilla & New Mexican chili peppers & added 2-3 oz. of good 73% dark chocolate in addition to cocoa/sugar already in recipe. *Used chicken breasts sprinkled with lots of cumin browned in oil, sliced into strips & simmered in sauce. This sauce is delicious! Mexican friend that's a lifetime mole fan pronounced it really, really good with awesome flavor/texture. Thanks everyone for the tips. Try this recipe...you'll love it.

