A very forgiving recipe but not necessarily easy. Plan to have an hour or two the first time you make it plus lots of dishes. The other comments about the tomatos were accurate so be very careful how much you add. Otherwise, use all the onions as they give body and sweetness. I used dark chocolate instead of cocoa and it was great. It makes alot of sauce so plan to have leftovers unless you are feeding ten. I roasted chicken thighs and then cut up the meat. Excellent. I plan to get a supermarket chicken later in the week for an easy weeknight supper. I also made a peach salsa with it and it was a perfect counterpoint to the spices in the mole. If you like mole, try this recipe and use spices and chiles that you have like in other dishes. Good luck.

