Rating: 4
Wow! After feeling daunted by the "three-day authentic mole" recipe on this site, I decided that the easy version was at least worth a try. It was, as promised, easy as well as delicious. Based on other reviewers' comments, I was wary of adding the can of tomatoes, and instead opted for 1 1/2 cups of tomato puree. That seemed to be a great amount in terms of taste, texture, and color, so I will stick with that alteration in the future. Also, since we had no chili powder, I roasted three fresh pasilla chiles and ground them into a paste (made about 1 1/2 Tbsp). Nice smokiness, and light on the heat (though I have a feeling that tomorrow's mole may be hotter as the peppers 'age'). I used only 2 cups chicken stock...think the third cup would have made it too thin. Part of achieving the rich color may have something to do with your patience in browning the onions. I went for a color closer to 'brown' than 'golden brown.' We shredded a rotisserie chicken instead of the wings: moist and easy! Will definitely make again - though it will be awhile, since we have 2 cups of mole left over (no complaints!).

