Rating: 3
Yum! Been craving mole and there are no good Mex. restaurants in Belgium! This was the first time I ever made it myself and was very happy with results after tweaking a bit. Based on previous reviews, I cut back on the onion and tomato (used about a cup of onion and only about 1/3 can of chopped tomatos, just enough to redden up the brown color a little. Also, I decided no way was I going to have mole without the texture of ground nuts! so I also thru into the blender a handful of peanuts and a handful of pumpkin seeds (after first roasting and browning them a bit deeper in a skillet). Also, to counteract the richness of the nuts and the power of the spices and peppers, I decided some more fruity tang would be called for and so a couple of strips of chopped lemon skin went in to the blender also. Excellent!

